body:
## Using Marv is easy

* Use the File->Open menu to select a markdown file;
* Marv will convert the markdown into HTML and render it in the window;
* Edit the markdown file with any editor you like;
* When you save the markdown file in your editor, Marv will notice and update it's HTML rendering.

That's all there is to it.

### Authors and Contributors
Drafted by @davidalpert because although he likes MarkdownPad he just couldn't write comfortably without Vim.

### Support or Contact
Having trouble with Marv? Create an issue at Check out the documentation at https://github.com/davidalpert/marv/issues or fork the code and send me a pull request.
